<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-28T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-28T23:00:00-05:00" n="620" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.30 Asiatic Fleet/962: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stanton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-29T12:00:00+08:00">November
                                    29, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 2—5:59
                                a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1798. Admiral Glassford and staff left last night aboard the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Luzon</hi> for Manila. The <hi rend="italic">Luzon</hi> was accompanied by the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Oahu</hi>. U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Wake</hi> arrived from Hankow
                            yesterday afternoon. Under orders issued by Admiral Hart the <hi rend="italic">Wake</hi> has been partly decommissioned and is to
                            remain in Shanghai to maintain radio communications.</p>
                        <p>Sent to the Department. Repeated to Chungking, Peiping and Manila.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stanton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>